---
---
<section class="section-sm">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto fade-in">
      <div class="card border-border/50">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-2xl mt-0.5">&#x1f512;</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-1">How your data works</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mb-4">OpenMind runs on your laptop. There is no OpenMind server.</p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-2.5 text-xs">
              <div>
                <span class="text-text-primary font-medium">Stays on your machine:</span>
                <div class="text-text-secondary mt-1 space-y-0.5">
                  <div>&check; Config, profile, and state files</div>
                  <div>&check; Resume PDF &mdash; never uploaded</div>
                  <div>&check; No OpenMind server or telemetry</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <span class="text-text-primary font-medium">Sent to your LLM provider:</span>
                <div class="text-text-secondary mt-1 space-y-0.5">
                  <div>&bull; Your messages, course list, and profile fields</div>
                  <div>&bull; Tool results like Canvas data, PDFs, and web pages</div>
                  <div>&bull; Gmail, Slack, Calendar, Todoist, or notes content when you ask</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-4">
              API tokens stay in local config and go only to the service they authenticate with.
              bCourses, Gmail, and Slack are read-only. Google Calendar can create events.
              Run <code class="text-text-secondary">openmind privacy</code> for the full breakdown.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
